hopobject.body: How do you do? inkbox ink review Why? Studies over the last few years have suggested that the brain uses non-REM sleep time to recharge its batteries. New evidence from sleeping patterns in hibernating lemurs published in PLOS ONE this week strengthens the link between a chemical recharge in brain cells and the need for sleep to survive. On the flip side, since the metabolism is slowed in hibernators, researchers are starting to think they don't need as much sleep.
